\f0\fs28 \cf2 \cb3 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Do you want to be Rich, or do you want to be King?\cb1 \
\cb3 You need to decide...\cb1 \
\
\cb3 Noam Wasserman talks about the tension between being Rich or King in The Founder\'92s Dilemmas.\cb1 \
\
\cb3 In business and at home, it\'92s the choice between control and growth.\cb1 \
\cb3 You can make every business decision.\cb1 \
\
\cb3 Or you can invest in your staff and colleagues so they grow beyond you.\cb1 \
\cb3 You can protect your pride and authority at home.\cb1 \
\
\cb3 Or you can invest in your family so they grow in confidence, ownership, and strength.\cb1 \
\
\cb3 This isn\'92t really about money or power.\cb1 \
\
\cb3 It\'92s about identity.\cb1 \
\
\cb3 How do you see yourself?\cb1 \
\cb3  As the one who must decide, approve, and direct?\cb1 \
\cb3  Or as the one who develops others and makes lasting investments?\cb1 \
\
\cb3 And here\'92s where it connects.\cb1 \
\cb3 Are you making it about you? It\'92s not always about you!\cb1 \
\
\cb3 So much of our frustration shows up when we make it about us.\cb1 \
\cb3  My status.\cb1 \
\cb3  My control.\cb1 \
\cb3  My need to be right.\cb1 \
\cb3  My authority.\cb1 \
\
\cb3 But growth rarely happens when I make it about me.\cb1 \
\
\cb3 It happens when I step back so others can step up and become the best version of themselves possible.\cb1 \
\
\cb3 READ THIS: Their best version of themselves.\'a0Not their best version of me.\cb1 \
\
\cb3 This question follows us everywhere:\cb1 \
\
\cb3 Am I trying to be King\'85\cb1 \
\cb3 Or, am I richly building and investing in a team, a family, or a purpose bigger than me?\cb1 \
\
